Place potatoes in a large pot of water and boil until tender when pierced with a fork. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Butter a 9x3 inch casserole dish. In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, onion, cottage cheese, and sour cream. Transfer mixture to the prepared casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 30 to 40 minutes.